Since this section aims to compare the empirical equations for predicting PPV regarding the best fit, Table 4 lists the constants calculated via regression analysis. Figure 7 shows the relationship between measured and predicted PPV for all empirical equations. Table 5 further lists the performance assessments regarding the predictions to enable evaluating the empirical models’ accuracy. Based on Table 5, Eq. (7) shows the better performance than other empirical equations, and yields the R2, MSE, RSME, MAE, NMBE, MAPE, NS, IOA IOS and PI values of 0.6, 18.12, 4.26, 3.03, 2.68, 130.61, 0.6, 0.85, 0.63 and − 3.65 on the train set, respectively. Meanwhile, Eq. (7) yields the values of R2, MSE, RSME, VAF, MAE,NMBE, MAPE, NS, IOS, a20 and PI of 0.71, 5.64, 2.38, 0.72, 1.63, 1.98 244.01, 0.71, 0.83, 37.50 and − 1.66 on the test set, repsectively.Table 4
